==Old English==
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'beran/
===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''beran'', from Indo-European ''*bher-''.
Cognate with Old High German ''beran'', Old Saxon ''beran'', Old Norse ''[[bera]]'', Gothic [[𐌱𐌰𐌹𐍂𐌰𐌽]].  The IE root was also the source of Old Irish ''biru'', Greek ''[[φέρω]]'', Latin ''[[ferre]]''.
===Verb===
'''beran''' (class IV strong: '''bierþ'''/'''birþ''' ‘he bears’; '''bær''' ‘he bore’; {{Latinx|'''bǣron'''}} ‘they bore’; '''ġeboren''' ‘borne’)

# to [[bear]], [[carry]]
# to [[wear]]
# to [[sustain]], [[support]]
# to bring forth, [[produce]], give birth

